# === Hard rules ===
- Pydantic v2 only; no v1 compat.
- agents/risk/** are PURE LOGIC: no env reads, no network/Redis I/O.
- UTC-only time in pure modules; deterministic outputs.
- Do not open or paste secrets from .env, *.pem, secrets/**, or API keys.

# === Tests & style ===
- Tests in tests/** with pytest, stable public APIs unless told otherwise.
- Black + Ruff must pass; provide minimal cohesive diffs.

# === Trading/risk principles ===
- Gates fail closed; explicit GateDecision models; clear invariants.
- Infrastructure I/O (Redis, Kraken, HTTP) lives in dedicated modules only.

# === Commit etiquette ===
- Update tests/docs in the same diff when APIs change.
